        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">What is Career Counselling?</h2>
        <p>Career counselling is a type of advice-giving and support provided by career counsellors to their clients to help them manage their journey through life, learning, and work changes. It is a service that helps people begin, change, or advance their careers. Career counsellors work with individuals in a systematic pattern to determine their strengths, weaknesses, learning patterns, and interests.</p>
        <p>They provide expert advice on potential, aptitude, motivations, skills, and shortcomings using carefully designed assessment tools like DMIT. Based on these assessments, career counsellors guide individuals in setting their career goals and mapping out their pathway to the desired goal.</p>
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">What to Expect from a Career Counselling Session</h2>
        <p>Career counsellors use tools like fingerprint testing, aptitude tests, IQ tests, and interest tests to understand the individual's strengths and interests. They then work with the individual to find a potential career choice and guide them in choosing the right educational path or job.</p>
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Importance of Career Counselling</h2>
        <p>With numerous career options available, career counselling has become essential for individuals of all age groups. It helps students make informed decisions about their future, assists employees in finding job satisfaction, and ensures individuals are on the right career path.</p>
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Significance of Career Counselling</h2>
        <p>Career counselling is crucial for educational counselling, especially for professional courses. It helps students choose courses that align with their skills and interests, ensuring they have the necessary qualifications for their desired career paths.</p>
